Made this to go with Beef tenderloin with port sauce described on this site. The port sauce also has shallots, so it seemd like a good match. It was very good - a bit more elegant than regular mashers, but even the purists in the family (who want their mashed potatoes with butter, milk and not much else) liked them. I cooked the shallots the day before. I chopped them in the food processor before cooking, and cooked them a long time over low heat - to ensure they didn'g get crispy. I poured about half the milk (actually used 1/2 and 1/2 for this)into the skillet and scraped up the bits after removing the shallots. Poured it over the cooked shallots and left in the fridge until the next day - then reheated in micro before adding to mashed potatoes.

