Rating: 4
Everyone loved these mashed potatoes. To avoid the tummy aches that some people get from having too many onions, I baked the unpeeled shallots, drizzled with olive oil and covered, for one hour in a 350 oven. After they have cooled, peel off the leathery layer of peel, and cut off the dark ends. Chop the remaining baked shallots finely and have them ready when making the dish. Let them simmer in the butter while the potatoes are cooking, then fold them in after the mashing is done. Really wonderful, just as amazing the next day in the potatoe pancakes. Had these with the Chicken Marsala recipe from this same site. Definitely a keeper.

